{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox video game |title = East vs. West – A Hearts of Iron Game |image = East vs. West - A Hearts of Iron Game box art.jpg |image_size = 250px |developer = BL-Logic<ref name=" FAQ ">{{cite web|url=http://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/showthread.php?627705-FAQ-Thread&p=14252921&viewfull=1#post14252921|title=Official FAQ|publisher=Paradox Plaza}}</ref> |publisher = [[Paradox Interactive]] |designer = |engine = Clausewitz Engine<ref name=" announcement ">{{cite web|url=http://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/showthread.php?617940-East-vs.-West-A-Hearts-of-Iron-Game!&p=14044430&viewfull=1#post14044430|title=Official Announcement|publisher=Paradox Plaza}}</ref> |released = Cancelled<ref name=Cancellation>{{cite web|last=Wester|first=Frederik|title=A joint statement from BL Logic and Paradox Interactive|url=http://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/showthread.php?760477-A-joint-statement-from-BL-Logic-and-Paradox-Interactive!{{!}}|publisher=Paradox Plaza|accessdate=6 March 2014}}</ref> |genre = [[Real-time strategy|Real-time]] [[Grand strategy wargame|grand strategy]] |modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]] |platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]] }} '''''East vs. West – A Hearts of Iron Game''''' was a planned [[grand strategy wargame]] set during the [[Cold War]] era between 1946–1991.<ref name=Cancellation />
== Gameplay == ''East vs. West'' was not an expansion for ''[[Hearts of Iron III]]'', but rather intended as a standalone game.<ref name="FAQ"/>
''East vs. West'', like many of its predecessors in the ''Hearts of Iron'' series, would have allowed for the player to take control of and manage a country including its political, diplomatic, espionage, economic, military, and technological aspects. In contrast to previous installments in the ''Hearts of Iron'' series, the game was to be set in the Cold War era, and not focus mainly on [[Total war|large-scale warfare]]. The use of [[nuclear weapons]] in game would have been possible, but limited by a [[DEFCON|nation's state of emergency]].{{cn|date=April 2018}}
=== Features === The main focus of the game were the diplomatic, political, economic, military and espionage aspects of countries during the Cold War period and the decisions the player make in regards to them.
Confirmed features included: * New espionage system utilizing "spy cards".<ref name=espionage>{{cite web|title=East vs West Developer Diary 8 - Espionage: HUSH HUSH|url=http://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/showthread.php?727362-East-vs-West-Developer-Diary-8-Espionage-HUSH-HUSH|publisher=Paradox Interactive}}</ref> * An extended political module.<ref name=politics>{{cite web|title=East vs West Developer diary 5 - The Essence of your People|url=http://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/showthread.php?679302-East-vs-West-Developer-diary-5-The-Essence-of-your-People|publisher=Paradox Interactive}}</ref> * A [[Doomsday Clock]] indicating how close the in game world is to total destruction. * The presence of the [[United Nations]] to intervene in global events. * The ability to customize ships.<ref name=shipeditor>{{cite web|title=East vs West Developer diary 4 - Master of the Seas|url=http://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/showthread.php?669564-East-vs-West-Developer-diary-4-Master-of-the-Seas|publisher=Paradox Interactive}}</ref> * [[Nuclear arms race]] and [[Nuclear warfare|warfare]] is expanded by a nuclear mapmode, [[uranium]] as a resource, factories ([[centrifuge]]s) to produce enriched fission material, [[ICBM]]s that can be launched from silos, [[nuclear submarine]]s, and a [[Big red button|red button]].<ref name=nuclear>{{cite web|title=East vs West Developer diary 7 - The Big Bang|url=http://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/showthread.php?688670-East-vs-West-Developer-diary-7-The-Big-Bang|publisher=Paradox Interactive}}</ref>
The game was expected to retain many features included in ''Hearts of Iron III'', such as control over the armed forces, the strategic warfare system, user mods-friendliness, and a multiplayer system with up to 32 players.<ref>{{cite web|title=East vs. West Features|url=http://www.paradoxplaza.com/games/east-vs-west|publisher=Paradox Interactive}}</ref>
== Cancellation == No release date was scheduled for ''East vs. West'' after the initial Q1 2013 release date was missed, though following a decision to cut major features including multiplayer functionality from the game, Paradox hoped to offer a pay-what-you-want public beta in March 2014.<ref name="beta ">{{cite web|url=http://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/showthread.php?749660-Regarding-the-future-of-East-vs-West-The-Beta-and-Release-Date|title=Regarding the future of East vs West - The Beta and Release Date|publisher=Paradox Plaza}}</ref> The cancellation of ''East vs. West'' was announced in a joint statement on 6 March 2014 by BL Logic and Paradox Interactive, citing multiple delays in the project.<ref name=Cancellation/>
