{{Italic title|force=true}} {{Infobox film | name = Fire from the Heartland: The Awakening of the Conservative Woman | image = Fire from The Heartland DVD cover.jpg | alt = | caption = DVD coverart | film name = | director = [[Steve Bannon|Stephen K. Bannon]] | producer = {{ubl|[[David N. Bossie]]|Stephen K. Bannon}} | writer = Stephen K. Bannon | screenplay = | story = | based on = <!-- {{based on|title of the original work|writer of the original work}} --> | starring = {{ubl|[[Michele Bachmann]]|[[Deneen Borelli]]|[[Ann Coulter]]|[[S. E. Cupp]]|[[Dana Loesch]]|[[Cynthia Lummis]]}} | narrator = | music = David Cebert | cinematography = Matthew A. Taylor | editing = Matthew A. Taylor | studio = {{ubl|[[Citizens United Productions]]|Victory Media}} | distributor = | released = {{Film date|2010|9|22}} | runtime = 84 minutes | country = United States | language = English | budget = | gross = }} '''''Fire From the Heartland: the Awakening of the Conservative Woman''''' is a 2010 [[Cinema of the United States|American]] [[documentary film]] written and directed by former [[Breitbart News]] LLC executive chairman [[Steve Bannon]], and produced by [[David N. Bossie]] for [[Citizens United Productions]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Green|first1=Joshua|title=Palin Filmmaker Spreads His Bets to Bachmann|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2011/07/palin-filmmaker-spreads-his-bets-to-bachmann/242523/|publisher=The Atlantic|accessdate=7 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Henry|first1=Devin|title=Citizens United hawking movie starring Bachmann|url=http://www.minnpost.com/minnpotus/2011/07/citizens-united-hawking-movie-starring-bachmann|publisher=[[MinnPost]]|accessdate=7 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Ziganto|first1=Lori|title=‘FIRE FROM THE HEARTLAND’ BURNS BRIGHT DESPITE LIBERAL VENOM|url=http://humanevents.com/2010/10/05/fire-from-the-heartland-burns-bright-despite-liberal-venom/|publisher=[[Human Events]]|accessdate=7 August 2014}}</ref> The documentary stars [[Michele Bachmann]], [[Deneen Borelli]], and [[Ann Coulter]], and focuses on female participation in [[conservative politics]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cogan|first1=Marin|title=Film focuses on women of the right|url=http://www.politico.com/news/stories/0910/42256.html|publisher=[[Politico]]|accessdate=7 August 2014}}</ref>
==Background== Bannon was inspired to create the documentary after seeing [[Governor of Alaska|former Alaskan governor]] [[Sarah Palin]] run as [[John McCain|John McCain's]] vice president running mate in the [[2008 United States presidential election]].<ref name=FN>{{cite web|last1=McKay|first1=Hollie|title=Filmmaker Spotlights Role of Women in Conservative Movement|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2010/10/04/fire-heartland-sarah-palin-conservative-women-bannon/|publisher=[[Fox News]]|accessdate=7 August 2014}}</ref> In exploring the [[Tea Party movement]], the film interviews only women. The sole male voice heard in the film is from a clip of an on-air rant by [[CNBC]]'s [[Rick Santelli]] from a February 2009 broadcast.<ref name="Wall Street Journal"/>
==Synopsis== The documentary looks at the idea of the conservative political female in the United States and how they have impacted and been impacted by the [[Tea Party movement]]. Bannon interviews women from different socioeconomic backgrounds and how this has had an effect on their outlook on life and in politics, as well as what they believe what the future will bring and their opinions on how conservative politics and the Tea Party is portrayed in the media.<ref name="Wall Street Journal">{{cite news|last1=[[John Fund]]|title=Why Mama Grizzlies Run the Tea Party|url=http://archive.li/MK1RI|accessdate=24 July 2018|publisher=[[Wall Street Journal]]|date=October 23, 2010}}</ref>
